column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''Lobster Bisque ($98) n nScarlett never ceases to impress us with their creative and delicious dishes. Whilst most lobster bisques are served to you in a bowl with little to no ingredients inside, this one was the complete opposite. Inside the plate were big pieces of lobster meat, cherry tomatoes, crackers and more. The staff would also help you pour the hot lobster bisque over it, soaking the ingredients with its rich flavours.  The bisque was creamy and savoury, and it even went well with the complementary baguettes provided! (8.5 10) n n#HKFVWestern #HKFVTST #HKFVJordan''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b'' xe4 xb9 xbe xe6 x8b x8c xe9 xba xb5 dry noodles (large for NTD60 ~ HKD15) n xe8 x82 x89 xe7 x87 xa5 xe9 xba xb5 braised pork noodles (large for NTD70 ~ HKD18) n nThe portions are huge here so if you ordered a bunch of side dishes as well like we did, it might be best to stick to a small serving of noodles. We had trouble finishing all the delicious food. The noodles are so tasty, especially the dry noodles, which surprised me in particular as they appeared plain at first with only spring onion on top. nAside from the many items on the menu you can tick to order, they have a fridge full of side dishes too that you can pick from, which is where we got the pork dish. (9 10) n#HKFVtaiwan #HKFVtaipei #HKFVtaiwanese #HKFVnoodles''

column1: Image may contain: drink
column4: b''Thai Milk Tea ($29) n nThis street in causeway bay has a lot of these take out drinks and I xe2 x80 x99ve always been a fan of Thai milk tea so I had to try. The flavour was really concentrated and rich, and you can taste the slight roasted taste of the tea leaves, making it all the more authentic. My problem with this is that they either have a cup full of ice, or no ice at all. They claim that it xe2 x80 x99s because the milk tea is very concentrated and needs a cup full of ice to dilute it, which I sincerely doubt because I xe2 x80 x99ve never seen anyone wait until the ice has melted before drinking it, let alone a whole cup full of ice. Nevertheless, the drink itself was really good, and the cup is made of hard plastic so you can reuse it for other purposes. (9 10)  n#HKFVCWB #HKFVThai''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b'Braised pork rice (NTD30 ~ HKD7.5 for small; 40 for medium; 50 for large) nMaximum flavour for minimal price! I xe2 x80 x99ve never had Taiwanese braised pork with as much flavour as this one! There isn xe2 x80 x99t a gigantic ton of pork but a small bite is enough to provide many times more flavour than other restaurant xe2 x80 x99s braised pork! (10 10) #HKFV10 #HKFVtaiwan #HKFVtaipei #HKFVtaiwanese'

column1: Image may contain: food and indoor
column4: b''Dry Aged Rib Eye ($398) n nIt xe2 x80 x99s dry aged steak season at Scarlett and they have several choices for parties of different sizes. We went with this rib eye, which was tender and perfectly cooked into a nice and pink medium rare. This also comes with a side dish, in which we chose spinach, and it was drenched in deliciously creamy sauce. (9 10) n n#HKFVWestern #HKFVTST #HKFVJordan''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''French toast (NTD330 ~ HKD83) nI loves this French toast for the soft, moist bread with fresh strawberry and caramel. (9.5 10) n#HKFVtaiwan #HKFVtaipei #HKFVwestern''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''Half tendon   half beef soup noodle (NTD270 ~ HKD68) nNo visit to Taiwan is complete without beef noodles! This restaurant used to be in a more rundown setting but since gaining fame it xe2 x80 x99s managed to move into a newer, comfier location. There xe2 x80 x99s a line outside for sure since it xe2 x80 x99s on the Michelin Guide but we only had to wait for around 20 minutes. Not a long wait for good beef and delicious broth! (8.5 10) n#HKFVtaiwan #HKFVtaipei #HKFVtaiwanese #HKFVnoodles''

column1: Image may contain: food and indoor
column4: b''Baked Pork Chop Rice in Bread ($68) and Milk Tea (+$14) n nWhat a mouthful. This dish has so many components that you would never imagine going together, but yet it does. The bread is hollow, with a crispy exterior and filled in with baked pork chop rice in tomato sauce. It xe2 x80 x99s pretty dry so that it doesn xe2 x80 x99t make the bread too soggy. Also, the milk tea here is a signature drink because their spherical ice cubes are frozen milk tea so it doesn xe2 x80 x99t dilute the flavour. (7 10) n n#HKFVKwaiFong #HKFVLocal''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''Cheese, pork patty, and egg (NT$75 ~ HKD 19) nFood in Taipei is so much! The Michelin restaurants I posted for were good bargains already, and plenty of affordable local food gives huge value for money too! nThe sandwich oozes so much cheese they give you plastic gloves to eat them with! It xe2 x80 x99s not just the heavy rich flavour of cheese either as the pork patty and egg are both flavourful in their own right! (10 10) n#HKFV10 #HKFVtaipei #HKFVtaiwan #HKFVsandwich''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''Char Siu, Prawn and Egg Rice ($59) n nThe simplest things in life can sometimes turn out to be the best. This classic Hong Kong meal is something that I find myself enjoying every so often and the one here is actually pretty good. The char Siu had flavour and texture, and the prawns were bouncy and meaty. I would say the egg could xe2 x80 x99ve been more runny and smooth though! (7.5 10) n n#HKFVKwaiFong #HKFVLocal''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b''Tasting menu (NTD3,750 ~ HKD940) nSpoiling myself last weekend, I visited yet another Michelin-star restaurant in Taipei - this time it was logy. The restaurant is smaller in size than RAW, which gave a more intimate feeling, especially since most customers sat at bar tables around the kitchen to watch the delicacies being prepared. nThe first starter was corn ice cream, served with sour cream and pumpkin powder. The cold dish was a welcome relief after walking in the heat outside, and the uncommon flavour reminded me of ice cream I once had in Hong Kong at Labmade, but softer. nThen came a scallop from Hokkaido with cucumber, lychee, and dried spring onion on top.  nThe third dish was inspired by tempura and was made up of bitter melon, dried fish, and fish liver sauce, with matcha powder sprinkled on it. I xe2 x80 x99m partial to bitter melon, but even if you xe2 x80 x99re not, there xe2 x80 x99s a complex mixture of flavours in the dish still. (10 10 overall) n#HKFV10 #HKFVtaiwan #HKFVtaipei #HKFVfusion''

column1: Image may contain: food
column4: b'Pan-fried Foie Gras on Toast with Figs ($138) and Dr. Kitty ($46 at Happy Hour) n nThe toast was served with the pan-fried Foie Gras with a piece of fig on top.  The combination of flavours worked really well and gave a perfect balance as a whole.  The fresh veggie on the side with balsamic vinegar also gave a refreshing and acidic taste to balance out the oiliness of the goose liver (7.5 10) n n#HKFVTaiPo #HKFVWestern'

column4: b''There xe2 x80 x99s a moving story behind #HongKong xe2 x80 x99s 1st public housing estate that many (including myself) are unaware of. n nOn Christmas Eve of 1953, a massive fire ripped through the shanties in #ShekKipMei. n nOver 50,000 people were left without any shelter. As a result, the old Colonial Government built a 29-block housing estate for the homeless. n nHighly recommend a visit to Shek Kip Mei & Sham Shui Po to get a true glimpse of Hong Kong life. n nUmbrella Chronicles (4 4) . #capturehongkong #discoverhongkong #localiiz #timeouthk . @passionpassport #PPShadows''

column4: b''Poster design by @milkxhake_org  n#Repost @hkuarchitecture  xc2 xb7 n#hkuarchitecture public lecture by Li Hu @open_lihu on April 16 - OPEN Questions. n nThe ever-changing realities of contemporary urban life, and the challenges they pose for humanity and the environment, call for an urgent rethinking of architectural precedent. To create spaces which reflect the kind of architectural complexity and urbanity present in cities today, particularly those in China, architecture must explore and embrace new opportunities for spatial reinvention. n. nArchitect Li Hu, founding partner of OPEN Architecture, will share with the audience observations drawn from more than a decade of architectural practice in Beijing. Through a series of questions xe2 x80 x94the starting points for some of OPEN xe2 x80 x99s latest projects on culture and education xe2 x80 x94Li will present his thoughts on how architecture can offer hope for the future by reacting to the challenges of today. n. nPoster design by @milkxhake_org  n#hkuarchitecture #publiclecture #lihu #openarchitecture #huangwenjing''

column1: Image may contain: text
column4: b''Really proud of this film ''Black To Techno'' directed by the one and only @jennnkiru Thank you so much for trusting me with the sound and for challenging me to take my skills to another level. I''m very confident that the people will appreciate what you have done for the culture.   xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 n--  xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 nFrom @jennnkiru xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x80 xa2  xe2 x80 xa2  xe2 x80 xa2  xe2 x80 xa2  xe2 x80 xa2  xe2 x80 xa2 xe2 x81 xa3 ndeeeeetroit ! so excited + honoured to finally bring #BLACKTOTECHNO back home to the 313 with a series of screenings taking place over memorial day weekend: xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 nsunday may 26th from 2:15pm, we xe2 x80 x99ll be taking over the museum of contemporary art detroit (@mocadetroit) with two screenings followed by an in-conversation between myself and UR xe2 x80 x99s Cornelius Harris (@undergroundresistance313) + Nandi Comer (@nandicomer). this screening will be in partnership with @gucci x @friezeartfair. xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 nmonday may 27th | 6pm we xe2 x80 x99ll be at @norwestgallery presenting WOMEN OF BLACK TO TECHNO: a screening + panel discussion exploring the history and influence of black women within techno culture. so honoured to be joined by an incredible panel of brilliant women brought to you by myself, @taylorraldridge @arts.black + DNA (@detnarrative   @invincibledet) xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 nentry to these events are free with suggested donations  **thursday may 23rd, @mocadetroit will also screen the film @ 6:30pm with an introduction by the legendary @derrickmay  xe2 x80 x94 humbled. xe2 x81 xa3 n xe2 x81 xa3 nsee u all soon + also can xe2 x80 x99t wait to shake w u all @movementdetroit too !! #blacktotechno #detroit #demf #undergroundresistance #jennnkiru''
